'''Deliverer's Sword Gauntlet''' is a [[Relic]] in the set [[World-Remaking Deliverer]].

==Description==
Phagousa's freezing seas engraved the vast shores of Styxia,<br />and the hero of deliverance has arrived at the crossing of the River of Souls, where a ghostly pale dragon transformed into a ferry to the netherworld.

Along the River of Souls, the spirits of the dead morph into sweet whispers, urging the hero to never return to the mortal realm.<br />''"You have subjugated the Titans of that world. Why not leave your legacy to successors?"''<br />Hearing these words, the sorrowful Deliverer replied in anguish:<br />''"O fallen souls who linger here, you've never considered how my desire to save the world outweighs my longing for reunion."''

Aboard the ferry, the Deliverer recalled memories of {{MC|f=her|m=his}} Flame-Chase journey,<br />''"Farewell, Thanatos of Death,''<br />''I pray you'll watch over my dearest friends, even though they never feared death."''<br />The Deliverer caressed {{MC|f=her|m=his}}  deerskin gauntlets, that still held the warmth of their fallen comrades.<br />{{MC|f=She|m=He}} drifted with the warm and humid west wind, from the shores blooming with Antila flowers to the mortal realm.

''"Cerces, please defend my rationality, so I need not face another shocking discovery."''<br />That experience of reviving from the dead was enough to prove to anyone that {{MC|f=she|m=he}} had the makings of a hero.<br />''"The wait won't be long now, my fellow Chrysos Heirs. I shall fulfill that unforgettable oath."''

The lands of Georios welcomed {{MC|f=her|m=his}} return, as the Flame-Chase journey continued.<br />Like dark clouds parting in the night, the morning star shall sparkle once more.

